---
import ElevationLayout from '../../layouts/ElevationLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/elevation/Hero.astro';
import Section from '../../components/elevation/Section.astro';
import { getProductBySlug } from '../../lib/products/registry';
import { productJsonLd } from '../../lib/structured-data';

const product = getProductBySlug('seven-requirements')!;
const jsonLd = productJsonLd(product, 'https://evoked.dev/products/seven-requirements');
---

<ElevationLayout
  title="Seven Requirements - Jurisdiction-Portable Governance"
  description="Seven governance requirements that persist if every framework disappears. Self-assessment scoring. The instrument that survives regulatory change. $49 PDF."
  structuredData={jsonLd}
>
  <Hero
    eyebrowParts={["Products", "Level 6 governance audit"]}
    headline="What governance persists if every framework disappears?"
    metaphor={["Seven requirements. Jurisdiction-portable."]}
    sub="The instrument that survives regulatory change."
  />

  <Section marker="FIG · I" heading="Why this exists">
    <p class="lede">
      We stripped away every regulation. The EU AI Act. NIST. Singapore. ISO
      42001. Then we asked what governance AI agents still require - by virtue
      of what they are and what they do.
    </p>
    <p class="pd-body">
      Seven requirements survived. Five are partially covered by existing
      frameworks but violated in practice. Two are absent from every published
      framework on earth. The industry has not rejected them. It has not
      considered them.
    </p>
    <p class="pd-body">
      Most organizations score between 0 and 4 out of 21. That number does not
      change when the regulation changes. These requirements are portable because
      they are principled, not jurisdictional.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · II" heading="What you get">
    <div class="pd-features">
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>7 requirements, 7 self-assessments</h3>
        <p>Each requirement with the evidence for why it persists, what the industry has built (and has not), and a concrete self-assessment question. Score what your architecture enforces.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>The two absences</h3>
        <p>Requirements 5 (Participation) and 7 (Sustainability) are absent from every framework on earth. We scored five major agent frameworks. All five scored zero on both. That gap defines our category.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>Grounded in research</h3>
        <p>Five research questions. Five frameworks scored. 2026 evidence base. Every requirement traces to a specific finding. Not theory - evidence.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>Framework-independent</h3>
        <p>These requirements do not depend on the EU AI Act, NIST, or any standard. They survive regulatory change. That is the point - and the commercial advantage.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · III" heading="The seven requirements">
    <div class="pd-pillars">
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">1</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Identity</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">Each agent distinguishable, persistent, architecturally enforced.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">2</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Integrity</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">Memory and self-knowledge protected. Corruption detectable. Both directions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">3</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Transparency</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">People know the agent exists. Explanations accessible to the person affected.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">4</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Recourse</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">A path to challenge that does not require knowing the agent existed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar pd-pillar-flag">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">5</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Participation</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">The governed have a voice. <strong>Industry score: zero across all five frameworks.</strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">6</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Non-extraction</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">Must not extract beyond what was meaningfully understood.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar pd-pillar-flag">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">7</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Sustainability</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">Governance survives regulatory change and platform transition. <strong>Industry score: zero.</strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · IV" heading="Buy the Seven Requirements">
    <div class="pd-purchase">
      <div class="pd-price">$49</div>
      <p class="pd-purchase-lead">PDF delivered immediately. Seven requirements with self-assessment scoring and industry baseline.</p>
      <a
        href={product.stripePaymentLink}
        class="pd-buy-cta"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
      >Purchase</a>
      <p class="pd-purchase-fineprint">
        Part of the
        <a href="/products/level-6-governance-toolkit">Level 6 Governance Toolkit</a>
        ($99, saves $97).
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="NOTA · BENE" heading="Go deeper" closing={true}>
    <div class="pd-upsell">
      <a href="/products/level-6-governance-toolkit" class="pd-upsell-card">
        <h3>Level 6 Governance Toolkit</h3>
        <p>All four Level 6 instruments - including the Seven Requirements - plus the Synthesis Guide. Combined 84-point scorecard.</p>
        <span class="pd-upsell-link">See the bundle &rarr;</span>
      </a>
      <a href="https://cal.com/cal.com-evoked/discovery-call" class="pd-upsell-card" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <h3>Discovery call</h3>
        <p>Free 30-minute call to discuss your score and the two absences your stack is missing.</p>
        <span class="pd-upsell-link">Schedule &rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </Section>
</ElevationLayout>

<style>
  /* Page-local: brass-emphasized pillar for the two industry-score-zero
     items (Requirements 5 and 7). The original page flagged these with
     accent-warm border color and brass strong text. */
  .pd-pillar-flag {
    background: color-mix(in oklab, var(--el-accent) 5%, transparent);
  }
  .pd-pillar-flag .pd-pillar-body h3 {
    color: var(--el-accent);
  }
  .pd-pillar-flag .pd-pillar-question strong {
    color: var(--el-accent);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .pd-purchase-fineprint a {
    color: var(--el-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }
  .pd-purchase-fineprint a:hover {
    color: var(--el-text);
    border-color: var(--el-accent);
  }
</style>
